  "diary": "Started the day cool and quiet—fed Miso, sipped tea, then walked over to Gas Works to scatter bread for the ducks. The park was already warming up, but peaceful. Spent a nice chunk of the morning at the library branch, browsing the new mysteries and catching up with the librarians. There's something about that place that still feels like home, even retired.\n\nLunched light because the heat was building—91 degrees by afternoon. I stayed inside with my novel and journal by the window, watching the smoke haze drift in from those BC fires. The air quality wasn't terrible, just enough to remind you something's burning somewhere far away.\n\nFood bank shift went well. Sorted donations, helped a few families—that work still matters to me, maybe more now. Walking home afterward, I could hear the first sounds of the concert crowd gathering at Gas Works. Decided to skip it; the heat and smoke weren't calling me out again. Instead, I made salmon, read more, and listened to music. Quiet evening. Good.",
